item.description:
To my Italian friends, except for Lorenzo who said he enjoyed this and didn&rsquo;t seem to be lying, you may look away.
&hellip;
We made this last week, adapting a recipe for &ldquo;drunken pasta&rdquo;, or pasta alla chiantigiana from the New York Times. It is spaghetti, cooked in a cup of red wine and water, with a tomato sauce simmered down with the rest of the wine. We served it with crispy pieces of guanciale, the cheek of the pig.
